<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - TROUBLESHOOTING - ENGINE EXHAUST TEMPERATURE (PYROMETER)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ENGINE EXHAUST TEMPERATURE (PYROMETER)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08035x_19.xml" xrefid="x0803514">PYROMETER</hotlnk>
                for circuit operation.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pyrometer Reads Full Scale With Key ON</title>
            <para>If the circuits to the Pyrometer control module have an open circuit (thermocouple burns out for
                example), the control module produces a full scale signal to the gauge.
            </para>
            <table id="t0803528" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Pyrometer Reads Full Scale With Key ON</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.55in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.84in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.33in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Disconnect thermocouple leads from the module at connector (492). Measure
                                    resistance to ground at the 16 gauge red and the yellow wires.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>16 gauge red and yellow wires to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>> or = 100K Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Replace the thermocouple/lead assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>At connector (492), measure the resistance between the red and yellow wires in the
                                    thermocouple assembly.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Red and yellow wires</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3 to 4 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Replace the pyrometer control module.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Replace the thermocouple assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pyrometer Reads LOW Or NO Exhaust Temperature</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08035x_19.xml" xrefid="x0803514">PYROMETER</hotlnk>
                for circuit operation.
            </para>
            <table id="t0803529">
                <title>Pyrometer Reads LOW Or NO Exhaust Temperature</title>
                <tgroup cols="7">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="sqcolumn1" colwidth="0.60in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="sqcolumn2" colwidth="0.60in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="sqcolumn3" colwidth="1.68in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="4" colname="sqcolumn4" colwidth="0.76in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="5" colname="sqcolumn5" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="6" colname="sqcolumn6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="7" colname="sqcolumn7" colwidth="1.32in" colsep="1"/>
                    <thead valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check 10A fuse F10-A for open condition.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>F10-A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Fuse OK?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then replace fuse.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (15) measure voltage to ground at circuit 25.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15) circuit 25 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of NO or LOW voltage in circuit 25 from fuse F10-A, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (15) measure voltage between circuits 25 and 25-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15) circuits 25 and 25-G</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 25-G between connector (15) and (454) ground adapter, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off/On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect (15) to control module and disconnect (423) from gauge cluster. KEY ON-
                                    Measure voltage to ground at connector (423) circuit 25A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(423) circuit 25A to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>7.7 to 8.7 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Step 6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Step 5.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At control module side of connector (15) measure voltage to ground at 18GA blue
                                    wire.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15) 18GA blue wire to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>7.7 to 8.7 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 25A between connectors (15) and (423), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace control module.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance of circuit 25B between connectors (15) and (423).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15) and (423) circuit 25B</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 25B, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (423) measure resistance to ground at circuit 25-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(423) circuit 25-GA</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 25-GA between connector (423) and (454) ground adapter,
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Run engine to generate exhaust temperature. Use thermometer to measure. Measure
                                    voltage to ground at back of connector (15) 18GA Brown wire. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803513">Figure 13</hotlnk>
                                    for expected voltage.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15) 18GA brown wire</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Expected voltage?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the module.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <figure id="f0803513" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803513" filename="../figg08/G0803513.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Voltage Output Chart</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
